  <p id="sK26ob">2023’s edition of Summer Games Done Quick (SGDQ), the annual weeklong speedrunning marathon for charity, kicks off on Sunday, and I can’t wait. For an entire week, SGDQ features hit after hit of speedrunners beating video games extremely fast or breaking them in unfathomable ways, and it’s a delightful way to learn more about some of my favorite video games and get introduced to new ones.</p>
<p id="G76fxS">This year’s show kicks off with a run of <a href="https://www.theverge.com/23471283/sonic-frontiers-review-sega-platforming"><em>Sonic Frontiers</em></a>, 2022’s “open zone” entry in the Sonic franchise, which seems apt. Gotta go fast, right? And rest of <a href="https://gamesdonequick.com/schedule/43">the schedule</a> is packed with potential hits; personally, I’ve got my eye on the runs for <em>Peggle Deluxe</em>, <em>Returnal</em>, <em>Kaizo Monkey Ball</em>, and a bonus <em>blindfolded</em> run of <em>The Legend of Zelda: Breath of the...</em></p>
